1
00:00:07,033 --> 00:00:08,700
<i> You embarrassed me again!</i>

2
00:00:08,833 --> 00:00:10,867
<i>I don't even understand
how you ended up my kid!</i>

3
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:12,900
<i>They said my child
and I are in danger.</i>

4
00:00:13,033 --> 00:00:13,967
<i> Death threat?</i>

5
00:00:14,100 --> 00:00:15,600
<i>Why are we only hearing
about this now?</i>

6
00:00:15,733 --> 00:00:17,133
<i> Dad, please.</i>

7
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:19,533
<i>I don't want anything bad
happening to my niece.</i>

8
00:00:19,667 --> 00:00:21,000
<i> If I hadn't said that,</i>

9
00:00:21,133 --> 00:00:22,733
<i>do you think they'd let us
stay here?</i>

10
00:00:22,867 --> 00:00:24,600
<i> You can't eat pride.</i>

11
00:00:24,733 --> 00:00:27,000
<i>I only agreed to let you move in
because of Ashley.</i>

12
00:00:27,133 --> 00:00:29,800
<i>You cause one problem,
and we're done.</i>

13
00:00:29,933 --> 00:00:31,100
<i> Paolo!</i>

14
00:00:31,233 --> 00:00:34,133
<i>Look, Mom, your favorite
daughter-in-law is here, too.</i>

15
00:00:34,300 --> 00:00:35,667
<i> Marj, really?</i>

16
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:37,567
<i> You know I have guests,</i>

17
00:00:37,700 --> 00:00:41,867
<i>and you come out looking
like that?</i>

18
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,100
Excuse me.

19
00:00:43,233 --> 00:00:45,100
I just need to attend
to something.

20
00:00:49,433 --> 00:00:50,767
She seems to be a good person.

21
00:00:50,900 --> 00:00:52,700
Of course.

22
00:00:52,833 --> 00:00:57,133
But she doesn't exactly fit
CEO's wife aesthetic.

23
00:00:57,267 --> 00:00:58,533
- Actually...
- Right?

24
00:00:58,667 --> 00:01:00,867
- Right?
- You know what?

25
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:03,400
Paolo fell for her heart.

26
00:01:03,533 --> 00:01:08,567
You know, true love isn't just
about looks, right?

27
00:01:17,133 --> 00:01:19,300
Thea, have some tea.

28
00:02:23,933 --> 00:02:25,233
Marj?

29
00:02:30,767 --> 00:02:32,567
Marj.

30
00:02:32,700 --> 00:02:34,333
Why are you crying?

31
00:02:36,467 --> 00:02:38,467
It's nothing, I'm just tired.

32
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:39,433
Oh, come on.

33
00:02:39,567 --> 00:02:42,367
Don't mind
what mom's friends said.

34
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:43,900
That's just how they are.

35
00:02:44,033 --> 00:02:45,700
They always have something
to say.

36
00:02:48,367 --> 00:02:49,633
But to be fair...

37
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:51,967
your priorities
are different now.

38
00:02:52,933 --> 00:02:54,867
Jasmine comes first, right?

39
00:02:56,133 --> 00:02:59,367
Instead of, you know,
dressing up and socializing.

40
00:03:00,067 --> 00:03:02,400
Honestly, Marj,
you made the right call

41
00:03:02,533 --> 00:03:05,467
of not going to the dinner party
for Mr. Zaragoza.

42
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:07,033
It will just stress you out.

43
00:03:08,667 --> 00:03:09,733
Thea, I was just thinking...

44
00:03:09,867 --> 00:03:12,633
Oh, please, I'll handle Paolo.

45
00:03:12,767 --> 00:03:15,133
I'm used to that crowd.

46
00:03:15,267 --> 00:03:19,800
And I just don't want you
feeling out of place.

47
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:24,300
Especially with people
who look you up and down.

48
00:03:27,467 --> 00:03:31,400
Marj, I just don't want you
getting hurt again.

49
00:03:32,667 --> 00:03:35,567
I don't want you hearing
those comments...

50
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:39,667
well, you know.

51
00:03:41,533 --> 00:03:43,333
You should just rest.

52
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:46,667
I'll take care of Paolo
at the party.

53
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:22,167
Edna, Rose, Ma'am Yolly, Weng,

54
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:24,267
we've got someone new
in the house.

55
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:25,167
Her name's Cheche.

56
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:27,600
I recommended her
to our employers.

57
00:04:27,767 --> 00:04:29,133
Good thing you're here.

58
00:04:29,267 --> 00:04:31,067
Welcome, Cheche.

59
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:32,133
Thank you.

60
00:04:32,267 --> 00:04:34,500
Oscar told me I'm needed here

61
00:04:34,633 --> 00:04:37,067
since there are new people
moving in.

62
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:38,933
Oh, really?

63
00:04:39,067 --> 00:04:41,033
You're updated?

64
00:04:41,167 --> 00:04:44,667
Well, of course, she needs
to know who to focus on.

65
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:46,267
Oh, okay.

66
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:49,200
So you'll be focusing
on Sir Edward and Ma'am Thea?

67
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:51,400
Yes, and Ashley.

68
00:04:51,533 --> 00:04:55,933
They said they need extra help.

69
00:04:56,067 --> 00:04:57,867
And I'm really good
at taking care of things.

70
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,167
Yes, so much.

71
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:01,767
Oh, really?

72
00:05:01,900 --> 00:05:03,433
Okay.

73
00:05:03,567 --> 00:05:04,833
Good luck.

74
00:05:04,967 --> 00:05:06,500
Hope you can handle it here.

75
00:05:06,633 --> 00:05:08,767
Being a house help isn't easy.

76
00:05:19,567 --> 00:05:20,633
Thea's taking so long.

77
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:25,400
Sorry, you know how she is.

78
00:05:25,533 --> 00:05:27,200
At events like this,

79
00:05:27,333 --> 00:05:28,767
she takes forever to get ready.

80
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:30,867
It's fine, bro.

81
00:05:54,067 --> 00:05:55,133
There she is.

82
00:05:57,700 --> 00:05:58,667
Hon.

83
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:04,833
Hon, you look amazing.

84
00:06:21,833 --> 00:06:23,267
Hi, Paolo.

85
00:06:54,333 --> 00:06:56,867
I hope it's not too late
to change my mind.

86
00:07:00,133 --> 00:07:01,767
I'm coming with you.

87
00:07:03,667 --> 00:07:04,767
Wow.

88
00:07:05,467 --> 00:07:06,533
Marj.

89
00:07:10,867 --> 00:07:12,333
Nice!

90
00:07:12,467 --> 00:07:14,000
So you're coming after all.

91
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:15,433
Good for you.

92
00:07:17,333 --> 00:07:18,567
You look beautiful.

93
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:27,400
Let's go.

94
00:07:35,867 --> 00:07:37,067
Thank you for coming.

95
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:38,667
Glad you could make it.

96
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:40,567
It's been a while, Marj.

97
00:07:40,700 --> 00:07:42,167
It really is, thank you.

98
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:44,867
- There's my dear friend.
- We'll leave you two, okay?

99
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,767
- Sure.
- Enjoy yourselves.

100
00:07:51,267 --> 00:07:53,133
Thank you, Love.

101
00:07:53,267 --> 00:07:54,367
I'm so happy.

102
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:59,667
You have no idea how much
I missed this.

103
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:02,533
Like this...

104
00:08:02,667 --> 00:08:04,233
Just the two of us...

105
00:08:04,367 --> 00:08:05,633
Like before.

106
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:11,633
We promised each other
we'd fix this, Love.

107
00:08:11,767 --> 00:08:13,500
For Jasmine, too.

108
00:08:13,633 --> 00:08:16,267
That's why I need to take care
of myself.

109
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:19,500
So I can keep taking care of us.

110
00:08:19,633 --> 00:08:21,400
I'm just really glad
you're here.

111
00:08:40,900 --> 00:08:43,100
Marj, long time no see.

112
00:08:43,233 --> 00:08:45,933
You're glowing even more.

113
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:48,300
True, you look refreshed.

114
00:08:48,433 --> 00:08:49,467
What skincare are you using?

115
00:08:51,933 --> 00:08:53,667
Oh, please...

116
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:56,033
it's like you don't know Marj.

117
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:58,733
When there's an event,
she makes time.

118
00:08:58,867 --> 00:09:03,100
But at home?
Totally different story.

119
00:09:03,233 --> 00:09:05,267
You should see the before
and after.

120
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:08,067
But that's what happens
when you're a hands-on mom.

121
00:09:10,033 --> 00:09:12,300
Thea, you didn't have
to bring that up.

122
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:15,800
Hey, that's admiration.

123
00:09:15,933 --> 00:09:18,567
What you do isn't easy.

124
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:22,367
Balancing Jasmine and work?

125
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:24,567
They should know
how dedicated you are.

126
00:09:26,367 --> 00:09:27,533
Oh, Thea!

127
00:09:27,700 --> 00:09:28,667
Guess what?

128
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:33,200
We're planning to have
a quick getaway in Cebu!

129
00:09:33,333 --> 00:09:34,467
- Cebu?
- Next month.

130
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:37,700
- You should come with us.
- Oh my gosh, seriously?

131
00:09:38,567 --> 00:09:40,100
That sounds fun.

132
00:09:40,233 --> 00:09:41,167
I'm game.

133
00:09:41,300 --> 00:09:43,367
And I'll take you
to the best spots.

134
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:46,633
The food market in Lahug,
the beaches,

135
00:09:46,767 --> 00:09:49,567
and there's this super cute
new café.

136
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:51,633
There's so much to see in Cebu.

137
00:09:51,767 --> 00:09:53,533
Don't worry, I'll take care
of you guys.

138
00:09:53,667 --> 00:09:55,800
- Perfect!
- That's good!

139
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,267
Thea?

140
00:10:02,433 --> 00:10:05,900
Did you really just agree
to go to Cebu with Clarissa?

141
00:10:07,633 --> 00:10:08,767
Why not?

142
00:10:10,467 --> 00:10:12,233
Why would you say yes?

143
00:10:12,367 --> 00:10:14,033
What about the death threats?

144
00:10:14,167 --> 00:10:15,467
<i> Just leave us alone!</i>

145
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:19,667
<i> An investor told us
that if we ever go back to Cebu,</i>

146
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:21,867
<i>my child and I would be
in danger.</i>

147
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,800
<i> Stop bothering us!</i>

148
00:10:27,367 --> 00:10:32,700
Actually, I just said yes
to the invitation to be polite.

149
00:10:32,833 --> 00:10:35,433
What? I'm not really going,
okay?

150
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:37,167
And, of course,
I haven't forgotten

151
00:10:37,300 --> 00:10:40,300
about the death threats
from the loan sharks in Cebu.

152
00:10:40,433 --> 00:10:41,733
Loan sharks?

153
00:10:46,433 --> 00:10:47,467
Yes.

154
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:50,767
You told me the debt
was from investors.

155
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:53,967
And the death threats
came from them, too.

156
00:10:55,067 --> 00:10:56,600
Not loan sharks.

157
00:10:58,333 --> 00:11:03,433
Marj, we're going through
so much already.

158
00:11:03,567 --> 00:11:07,300
You know how it is,
sometimes the terms overlap.

159
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:12,500
There are investors, lenders,

160
00:11:12,633 --> 00:11:14,233
and all kinds of people
harassing us.

161
00:11:14,367 --> 00:11:15,900
- Your story's not lining up...
- Wait.

162
00:11:17,467 --> 00:11:19,033
Why are you triggering me?

163
00:11:20,767 --> 00:11:24,067
This is a party,
not an interrogation.

164
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:27,133
Why don't you grab a drink
and relax?

165
00:11:27,267 --> 00:11:30,133
Because your stories
don't add up.

166
00:11:30,267 --> 00:11:31,800
So what's the truth?

167
00:11:31,933 --> 00:11:34,667
Are there really death threats
or did you just make it all up?

168
00:11:38,233 --> 00:11:39,733
Why are you asking me that now?

169
00:11:40,633 --> 00:11:43,267
And why is this such a big deal
to you?

170
00:11:43,433 --> 00:11:44,467
Because it matters to me,

171
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:47,533
you made me believe
you were getting death threats.

172
00:11:47,667 --> 00:11:51,300
I talked to dad and Paolo
so you could stay in the house.

173
00:11:53,300 --> 00:11:54,767
Why?

174
00:11:54,900 --> 00:11:56,900
Did I force you to say that?

175
00:11:57,033 --> 00:11:58,567
No, right?

176
00:11:58,700 --> 00:12:00,000
That was your choice.

177
00:12:00,133 --> 00:12:02,233
So don't throw it in my face.

178
00:12:02,367 --> 00:12:04,067
This isn't about being indebted.

179
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:06,267
I'm just asking
what's the truth.

180
00:12:09,900 --> 00:12:14,900
Here's the truth, Marj,
you're not the only Torrecampo.

181
00:12:15,067 --> 00:12:16,533
I am, too.

182
00:12:16,667 --> 00:12:20,267
As long as my child and I
carry that last name...

183
00:12:21,633 --> 00:12:24,333
we have a place in that house.

184
00:12:24,467 --> 00:12:27,500
With or without death threats.

185
00:12:27,633 --> 00:12:31,800
Whether everything
I'm saying is true or not.

186
00:12:32,967 --> 00:12:34,467
There's nothing
you can do about it, Marj.

187
00:12:35,567 --> 00:12:37,533
You can't change the fact

188
00:12:37,667 --> 00:12:40,900
that we have a right
to live there.

189
00:12:41,700 --> 00:12:45,600
Thea, I'm not questioning
your right as a Torrecampo.

190
00:12:45,733 --> 00:12:47,033
What I don't like is

191
00:12:47,167 --> 00:12:50,967
you using me as a tool
for your lies.

192
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:53,433
So what now?

193
00:12:54,467 --> 00:12:56,400
You're gonna tell on me?

194
00:12:56,533 --> 00:12:58,533
Go ahead!

195
00:12:58,667 --> 00:13:00,367
You don't have any proof.

196
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:03,167
It's just your words
against mine.

197
00:13:04,667 --> 00:13:06,933
It's up to you, Marj.

198
00:13:07,067 --> 00:13:09,733
Do you really want to tear
this family apart again

199
00:13:09,867 --> 00:13:11,833
by badmouthing me?

200
00:13:11,967 --> 00:13:14,400
Telling the truth
isn't badmouthing.

201
00:13:14,533 --> 00:13:17,600
Stop playing the victim
and don't shift the blame on me.

202
00:13:17,733 --> 00:13:20,733
Then who am I supposed to blame
if we get kicked out?

203
00:13:21,733 --> 00:13:23,167
Can you live
with your conscience

204
00:13:23,300 --> 00:13:26,767
if Edward's dad disowns him?

205
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:29,933
And if Ashley's future
gets ruined?

206
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,633
So, Marj, if I were you,

207
00:13:36,767 --> 00:13:41,800
I'd think long and hard before
throwing accusations at me.

208
00:13:42,933 --> 00:13:45,000
Because I won't be the only one
who goes down.

209
00:13:46,533 --> 00:13:50,700
Edward and Ashley could get
dragged into this, too.

210
00:13:58,067 --> 00:13:59,300
What's going on here?

211
00:14:00,933 --> 00:14:02,967
Hon, is there a problem?

212
00:14:05,067 --> 00:14:06,400
Nothing.

213
00:14:06,533 --> 00:14:11,200
We were just reminiscing
about the good old days.

214
00:14:11,333 --> 00:14:12,400
Right, Marj?

215
00:14:15,167 --> 00:14:16,667
Yes...

216
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:18,033
the good old days.

217
00:14:19,133 --> 00:14:23,133
Some things never change.

218
00:14:26,933 --> 00:14:28,900
Love, let's go?

219
00:14:29,067 --> 00:14:31,467
Our colleagues want to say hi.

220
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:35,633
Oh, and don't forget
my advice...

221
00:14:35,767 --> 00:14:36,833
okay?

222
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:39,300
Let's go.

223
00:14:49,533 --> 00:14:52,333
The nerve of Thea,
lying to all of us like that.

224
00:14:52,467 --> 00:14:53,800
And Edward...

225
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:57,333
instead of calling out his wife,
he just went along with it.

226
00:14:57,767 --> 00:14:59,000
Dad needs to know about this.

227
00:15:00,367 --> 00:15:01,333
No, Love.

228
00:15:02,333 --> 00:15:03,467
I only told you

229
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:06,800
because I wanted you to see
Thea's true colors.

230
00:15:06,933 --> 00:15:10,167
But please, promise me,
don't tell dad.

231
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:12,000
Why not?

232
00:15:12,133 --> 00:15:15,067
Because I believe Edward
isn't at fault.

233
00:15:16,067 --> 00:15:18,567
He just gave in because
she's his wife.

234
00:15:19,700 --> 00:15:22,400
Love, I'm thinking
about their child, too.

235
00:15:22,533 --> 00:15:24,500
I feel bad for Ashley.

236
00:15:24,633 --> 00:15:28,800
She'll be the most affected
if they get kicked out.

237
00:15:28,933 --> 00:15:30,100
Yes.

238
00:15:31,133 --> 00:15:32,133
You're right.

239
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:37,600
Ashley shouldn't get dragged
into the mess her mom created.

240
00:15:39,467 --> 00:15:44,700
We can protect her better
and secure her future

241
00:15:44,833 --> 00:15:46,300
if she lives with us.

242
00:15:48,067 --> 00:15:49,933
I didn't realize you were
this concerned

243
00:15:50,067 --> 00:15:51,367
about Ashley's welfare.

244
00:15:53,400 --> 00:15:54,500
Of course.

245
00:15:56,367 --> 00:15:57,567
I'm concerned about her.

246
00:15:58,467 --> 00:15:59,733
She's my niece.

247
00:16:00,433 --> 00:16:02,067
Yes.

248
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:03,967
We have to look out for her.

249
00:16:04,967 --> 00:16:09,067
That poor kid. What if she picks
up her mom's bad behavior?

250
00:16:10,467 --> 00:16:13,867
I really regret believing
Thea had changed.

251
00:16:15,233 --> 00:16:16,300
And aside from the lying,

252
00:16:16,433 --> 00:16:20,300
I'm sure she's done something
even worse.

253
00:16:40,933 --> 00:16:43,067
How did Marj figure out there
weren't any real death threats?

254
00:16:44,667 --> 00:16:46,500
Obviously.

255
00:16:46,633 --> 00:16:49,067
She's always watching
my every move,

256
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:50,767
hanging on to everything I say.

257
00:16:51,700 --> 00:16:53,500
She just pretends to be
nice to me.

258
00:16:53,633 --> 00:16:55,467
Turns out she's totally fake.

259
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:58,167
Maybe you should've just talked
to her calmly.

260
00:16:58,300 --> 00:17:01,233
Maybe you should've told her
the real reason we did that.

261
00:17:01,367 --> 00:17:03,133
I'm sure she would understand.

262
00:17:03,267 --> 00:17:05,367
You shouldn't have argued
with her.

263
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:07,967
Oh, so now it's my fault?

264
00:17:08,100 --> 00:17:09,767
No, all I'm saying is,

265
00:17:09,900 --> 00:17:13,433
we need people on our side
instead of antagonizing them.

266
00:17:13,567 --> 00:17:16,233
What if Marj decides
to tell dad?

267
00:17:16,700 --> 00:17:18,167
Then we get kicked out
of the house!

268
00:17:19,467 --> 00:17:21,767
Don't pin this on me.

269
00:17:21,900 --> 00:17:25,200
If anyone messed up here,
it wasn't me.

270
00:17:25,333 --> 00:17:26,300
It was you.

271
00:17:27,267 --> 00:17:29,333
If you hadn't drowned us
in debt,

272
00:17:29,467 --> 00:17:32,233
if you'd managed the business
in Cebu properly,

273
00:17:32,367 --> 00:17:36,333
we wouldn't be
in this situation, right?

274
00:17:52,933 --> 00:17:54,100
<i> Ashley.</i>

275
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:59,300
Your school emailed
your transfer credentials.

276
00:17:59,433 --> 00:18:03,300
Why didn't you tell me
your Science grade dropped?

277
00:18:03,433 --> 00:18:04,700
Mommy, I'm sorry.

278
00:18:04,833 --> 00:18:06,800
The final exam was really hard.

279
00:18:06,933 --> 00:18:08,000
I struggled with it.

280
00:18:08,133 --> 00:18:09,567
But I tried my best.

281
00:18:09,700 --> 00:18:11,733
How are you supposed to transfer
to a Science School

282
00:18:11,867 --> 00:18:13,633
with grades like that?

283
00:18:16,367 --> 00:18:17,333
Wait.

284
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,900
Mommy, please don't.

285
00:18:21,033 --> 00:18:24,167
Didn't I tell you to stop
with the drawing?

286
00:18:24,333 --> 00:18:26,133
What do you want to be
in the future?

287
00:18:26,267 --> 00:18:28,000
Be someone flaking out
from school?

288
00:18:29,633 --> 00:18:32,500
Ashley, do you even know
how hard it is to fight

289
00:18:32,633 --> 00:18:34,300
for our place in this family?

290
00:18:35,233 --> 00:18:39,967
You need to focus on being
an academic achiever.

291
00:18:40,100 --> 00:18:42,367
There's no such thing
as a Torrecampo starving artist.

292
00:18:43,567 --> 00:18:44,500
I'm throwing this away

293
00:18:44,633 --> 00:18:46,433
before your life ends up
in the trash, too.

294
00:18:46,567 --> 00:18:48,000
- Please don't!
- I won't allow it!

295
00:18:48,767 --> 00:18:49,867
That's mine.

296
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:54,000
Those drawings are mine.

297
00:18:56,233 --> 00:18:57,667
I just showed them to Ashley

298
00:18:57,800 --> 00:19:00,900
because I asked for her opinion.

299
00:19:01,033 --> 00:19:02,767
Since when do you draw?

300
00:19:04,267 --> 00:19:06,967
Since forever, Auntie.

301
00:19:07,100 --> 00:19:09,000
I'm not sporty.

302
00:19:09,133 --> 00:19:11,233
I'm not athletic.

303
00:19:11,367 --> 00:19:13,100
I'm usually just at home.

304
00:19:14,033 --> 00:19:17,633
This is the only hobby
my mom lets me have.

305
00:19:17,767 --> 00:19:20,733
So please, don't throw it away.

306
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:22,800
I'm sorry.

307
00:19:24,867 --> 00:19:26,433
It's just that I've been
discouraging Ashley

308
00:19:26,567 --> 00:19:28,100
from drawing.

309
00:19:28,267 --> 00:19:29,667
She can't afford distractions

310
00:19:29,800 --> 00:19:31,100
from her priorities.

311
00:19:32,533 --> 00:19:33,933
I understand.

312
00:19:37,067 --> 00:19:39,400
Okay, you two go downstairs.

313
00:19:39,867 --> 00:19:41,033
Lunch is ready.

314
00:19:42,133 --> 00:19:43,133
We will.

315
00:19:51,567 --> 00:19:53,333
Why did you do that, Jas?

316
00:19:53,467 --> 00:19:55,067
We're best friends.

317
00:19:55,200 --> 00:19:57,233
And that's what best friends do.

318
00:19:57,367 --> 00:19:59,367
We've got each other's backs.

319
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:01,067
Thank you, Jas.

320
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:05,033
I'll never forget this.

321
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:37,567
Why do I feel like
there's tension in here?

322
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:43,400
Marj? Thea?

323
00:20:43,867 --> 00:20:45,667
Why can't you two even look
at each other?

324
00:20:45,800 --> 00:20:46,867
Is there a problem?

325
00:20:47,633 --> 00:20:49,200
No, Dad.

326
00:20:49,333 --> 00:20:51,167
I'm just a little
sleep-deprived.

327
00:20:51,300 --> 00:20:55,433
The farewell party
ended late last night.

328
00:20:58,267 --> 00:21:00,933
Marj and I are totally fine,
Dad.

329
00:21:01,067 --> 00:21:04,967
In fact, she's been so happy
ever since we moved in.

330
00:21:05,900 --> 00:21:07,500
Right, Marj?

331
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:19,700
- Grandfather.
- Yes, sweetheart?

332
00:21:19,833 --> 00:21:21,600
Remember Xander?

333
00:21:21,733 --> 00:21:23,033
- Yes.
- The grandson

334
00:21:23,167 --> 00:21:25,900
of your golf buddy?
Judge Jose Torralba?

335
00:21:26,033 --> 00:21:27,533
He's having a birthday
countdown later.

336
00:21:28,600 --> 00:21:31,700
Mom, can I please go?

337
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:33,367
I promise I'll be home by ten.

338
00:21:34,367 --> 00:21:35,300
Jas, no.

339
00:21:35,433 --> 00:21:37,467
I know Xander Torralba.

340
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:39,933
His parents are always getting
called to school

341
00:21:40,067 --> 00:21:44,867
because all that kid cares about
is friends and girls.

342
00:21:45,033 --> 00:21:47,200
That kid is trouble.

343
00:21:47,333 --> 00:21:49,133
Those are just rumors, Mom.

344
00:21:49,267 --> 00:21:51,367
Jasmine, the answer is no.

345
00:21:52,367 --> 00:21:54,967
I don't want you hanging out
with bad influences

346
00:21:55,100 --> 00:21:56,867
like that Xander.

347
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:25,467
Looking for a job?

348
00:22:26,900 --> 00:22:30,267
Just make sure you don't screw
things up again.

349
00:22:31,333 --> 00:22:33,300
This is your last chance,
Edward.

350
00:22:33,433 --> 00:22:37,200
If you fail again,
you're on your own.

351
00:22:38,500 --> 00:22:40,167
Do I really mean
nothing to you, Dad?

352
00:22:45,600 --> 00:22:47,000
Excuse me?

353
00:22:47,133 --> 00:22:48,600
Do you have any idea
how much it hurts?

354
00:22:51,033 --> 00:22:53,433
Not once have I ever heard
you say you're proud of me.

355
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:58,033
Not even once.

356
00:22:58,967 --> 00:23:00,667
Even when I was a kid.

357
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:03,067
Instead of giving me praise,

358
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:04,900
you pointed out
every weakness...

359
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:07,733
every mistake.

360
00:23:11,700 --> 00:23:14,667
Don't turn me into a villain
in your story, Edward.

361
00:23:15,633 --> 00:23:19,967
Everything I did
was for your own good.

362
00:23:20,533 --> 00:23:22,633
So you wouldn't grow up
entitled.

363
00:23:23,367 --> 00:23:24,433
What do you want?

364
00:23:25,667 --> 00:23:28,400
For me to applaud you
every time you mess up?

365
00:23:28,533 --> 00:23:31,600
I'm not asking you to praise
everything I do.

366
00:23:31,733 --> 00:23:33,300
All I'm saying, Dad,

367
00:23:33,433 --> 00:23:35,733
is that I wish I could feel like
I'm actually your son.

368
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:39,800
Not just some project
you need to fix.

369
00:23:40,967 --> 00:23:43,733
Not just a list of mistakes
you're trying to correct.

370
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:15,500
Jas?

371
00:24:18,567 --> 00:24:21,100
Hey, why are you crying?

372
00:24:25,700 --> 00:24:27,900
I noticed earlier
you weren't okay.

373
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:31,367
If you need anything,
someone to talk to,

374
00:24:31,500 --> 00:24:32,800
I'm here.

375
00:24:32,933 --> 00:24:34,967
Thank you, Auntie.

376
00:24:36,367 --> 00:24:38,467
To be honest...

377
00:24:38,600 --> 00:24:39,667
I still feel bad

378
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:42,367
because I really wanted
to go to that party.

379
00:24:45,467 --> 00:24:49,000
But mom still doesn't trust me.

380
00:24:49,133 --> 00:24:51,067
It's like it's easier
for them to say no

381
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:52,800
than to actually listen to me.

382
00:24:55,033 --> 00:24:58,633
I guess, it's something
I just have to get used to.

383
00:24:59,967 --> 00:25:01,200
No, Jas.

384
00:25:02,100 --> 00:25:04,567
You should never get used
to being treated like that.

385
00:25:05,567 --> 00:25:07,467
If they're worried about you,

386
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:09,167
that doesn't mean
they should stop you

387
00:25:09,300 --> 00:25:11,967
from doing the things you love.

388
00:25:12,100 --> 00:25:13,933
The things that make you happy.

389
00:25:14,900 --> 00:25:17,100
I just want to be normal.

390
00:25:17,967 --> 00:25:19,933
A little freedom.

391
00:25:20,700 --> 00:25:23,633
Even one night
where they let me out...

392
00:25:23,767 --> 00:25:25,633
where they actually trust me.

393
00:25:27,933 --> 00:25:29,567
You know what, Jas?

394
00:25:29,700 --> 00:25:32,200
Sometimes parents
just want proof.

395
00:25:33,267 --> 00:25:34,833
Proof that you can handle
yourself.

396
00:25:35,367 --> 00:25:37,200
Proof that you're responsible.

397
00:25:38,900 --> 00:25:41,000
But how are they supposed to see

398
00:25:41,133 --> 00:25:44,267
that if they never give you
a chance?

399
00:25:44,400 --> 00:25:47,700
So, how do I show them?

400
00:25:51,333 --> 00:25:54,433
If I were you?
I'd go to that party...

401
00:25:55,467 --> 00:25:57,867
and show them I can be
responsible.

402
00:25:58,000 --> 00:25:59,400
That I can handle myself.

403
00:26:00,100 --> 00:26:02,000
That I won't get into trouble.

404
00:26:03,967 --> 00:26:05,333
If you pull that off,

405
00:26:05,467 --> 00:26:07,633
they'll trust you more.

406
00:26:07,767 --> 00:26:10,500
They won't be so strict
and controlling anymore.

407
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:13,567
And next time you ask
permission?

408
00:26:14,567 --> 00:26:16,867
It won't even be an issue.

409
00:26:27,133 --> 00:26:28,667
If I caught you one more time,

410
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:31,167
teaching my daughter
to disobey me,

411
00:26:31,300 --> 00:26:32,767
I swear I won't hold back.

412
00:26:32,900 --> 00:26:35,200
And who are you to tell me
what I can or can't do?

413
00:26:35,333 --> 00:26:37,300
Are we really safe here?

414
00:26:37,433 --> 00:26:39,733
You know what, we need
a breather from this house.

415
00:26:40,833 --> 00:26:41,767
Bill, please.

416
00:26:41,900 --> 00:26:44,300
- Paolo.
- You want to go home, right?

417
00:26:44,467 --> 00:26:45,533
Here you go.

418
00:26:45,667 --> 00:26:46,833
Auntie Thea's right.

419
00:26:46,967 --> 00:26:50,333
Maybe I need to do something
to change your mindset.

420
00:26:50,467 --> 00:26:51,833
Come on, go with me.

421
00:26:51,967 --> 00:26:54,200
Didn't your mom already
forbid you, Jas?

422
00:26:54,333 --> 00:26:57,233
Sir Paolo, about Jasmine...

423
00:26:57,367 --> 00:26:59,867
She is missing.

424
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:01,100
We're going to push
this through.

425
00:27:01,233 --> 00:27:03,867
- Can we just go home already?
- Ashley, stop!

426
00:27:07,667 --> 00:27:10,433
Jasmine, can you hear me?

427
00:27:10,567 --> 00:27:11,767
Jasmine?

428
00:27:11,900 --> 00:27:14,367
Jasmine, can you hear me?
Jasmine?

429
00:27:15,300 --> 00:27:17,433
Jasmine.
